(60,58,'2013-07-26 16:03:07','2013-07-26 16:03:08','Leap Motion Controller',NULL,'A device for PC and Mac that uses motion controls to interact with apps and games designed for it.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(61,59,'2013-07-30 15:50:37','2013-07-30 15:52:52','Taito DS Paddle',NULL,'Taito\'s Arkanoid came bundled with a paddle controller that connected to the GBA slot (only in Japan). Other Taito games supported this device besides Arkanoid.','','','<h2>Compatible Games</h2><ul><li><a href=\"//www.giantbomb.com/arkanoid-ds/3030-21608/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-21608\">Arkanoid DS</a></li><li><a href=\"//www.giantbomb.com/space-bust-a-move/3030-25411/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-25411\">Space Bust-A-Move</a></li><li><a href=\"//www.giantbomb.com/space-invaders-extreme/3030-20501/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-20501\">Space Invaders Extreme</a></li><li><a href=\"//www.giantbomb.com/space-invaders-extreme-2/3030-25127/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-25127\">Space Invaders Extreme 2</a></li></ul>',0,NULL,0),
(62,60,'2013-08-13 16:32:01','2018-06-15 21:06:10','ASCII Gamecube Keyboard Controller',NULL,'A unique GameCube controller that was stretched to contain a full keyboard in the center.','','','<p>Released exclusively in Japan, this wired <a href=\"https://www.giantbomb.com/ascii-corporation/3010-805/\" data-ref-id=\"3010-805\">ASCII</a> controller was designed for use exclusively with <a href=\"/phantasy-star-online-episode-i-ii/3030-3040/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-3040\">Phantasy Star Online Episode 1 &amp; 2</a>. The keys allow include both Latin and Japanese characters, as well as all of the standard GameCube keys.</p><p>Later, an identical keyboard was produced by <a href=\"https://www.giantbomb.com/sammy-corporation/3010-569/\" data-ref-id=\"3010-569\">Sammy</a> for the release of Phantasy Star Online Episode 3.</p>',0,NULL,0),
(63,61,'2013-08-19 10:58:12','2013-08-19 10:58:12','Atari 5200 Trakball Controller',NULL,'Official Track Ball controller for the Atari 5200.  Not all Atari 5200 games work with the controller however.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(64,62,'2013-08-22 18:09:11','2014-03-01 00:02:16','Logitech Driving Force GT',NULL,'A Gran Turismo-branded racing wheel, compatible with PS2, PS3, and PC.','','','<h2>Overview</h2><h2>Features</h2><figure data-align=\"right\" data-size=\"small\" data-img-src=\"https://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/original/21/218838/2572061-logitech%20driving%20force%20gt.jpg\" data-ref-id=\"1300-2572061\" data-embed-type=\"image\" data-ratio=\"1\"><a class=\"fluid-height\" style=\"padding-bottom:100.0%\" href=\"https://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/original/21/218838/2572061-logitech%20driving%20force%20gt.jpg\" data-ref-id=\"1300-2572061\"><img alt=\"No Caption Provided\" src=\"https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/original/21/218838/2572061-logitech%20driving%20force%20gt.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/original/21/218838/2572061-logitech%20driving%20force%20gt.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\" data-width=\"640\"></a></figure><ul><li>Force feedback</li><li>900-degree steering</li><li>Real-time adjustment dial (only works with GT5P, GT5 and GT6)</li><li>Gas and brake pedals</li><li>Sequential stick shift</li><li>Paddle shifters</li></ul><h2>PC Requirements</h2><ul><li>Windows 8, 7, Vista or XP</li><li>20 MB of available hard disk space</li><li>CD-ROM drive</li><li>Available USB port</li></ul><h2>Game Compatibility</h2><h4>PS3</h4><ul><li><a href=\"/burnout-paradise/3030-5648/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-5648\">Burnout Paradise</a></li><li><a href=\"/dirt/3030-3916/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-3916\">Dirt</a></li><li><a href=\"/dirt-2/3030-24513/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-24513\">Dirt 2</a></li><li><a href=\"/dirt-3/3030-30383/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-30383\">Dirt 3</a></li><li><a href=\"/f1-2010/3030-25985/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-25985\">F1 2010</a></li><li><a href=\"/f1-2011/3030-34542/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-34542\">F1 2011</a></li><li><a href=\"/f1-2012/3030-37743/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-37743\">F1 2012</a></li><li><a href=\"/ferrari-challenge-trofeo-pirelli/3030-20936/\