(68,66,'2014-02-16 03:37:36','2015-09-10 12:06:29','Joyboard',NULL,'The first commercially available balance board controller for a video game console','','','<p>The Joyboard is a balance board controller developed by <a href=\"/amiga-corporation/3010-6153/\" data-ref-id=\"3010-6153\">Amiga Corporation</a> for the Atari 2600. A player stands on the board and leans in any direction, mimicking the action of a joystick. A port on the Joyboard allows a regular joystick to plug through, so the Joyboard doesn\'t need to be removed from the console when not in use. </p><p>Amiga released a single title, <a href=\"/mogul-maniac/3030-19825/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-19825\">Mogul Maniac</a>, for use with the Joyboard, but <a href=\"/off-your-rocker/3030-34775/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-34775\">Off Your Rocker</a> was developed for the controller, and sold through a third party. A third title, Surf\'s Up, was developed but never released. </p><p>The legacy of Joyboard includes other balance board controllers, such as the Roll n Rocker and the <a href=\"/wii-balance-board/3000-10/\" data-ref-id=\"3000-10\">Wii Balance Board. </a></p>',0,NULL,0),
(69,67,'2014-02-25 21:14:09','2022-08-01 17:46:43','PlayStation 2 Network Adaptor',NULL,'A combined dial-up modem and Ethernet adapter released for the PlayStation 2, which plugs into the console\'s expansion bay and allows online play in certain games. It also enables installation of the PlayStation 2 Hard Disk Drive.','','','<h2>Overview</h2><p>The Network Adaptor for <a href=\"/playstation-2/3045-19/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-19\">PlayStation 2</a> was released in July 2001 in Japan, August 2002 in North America, and June 2003 in Europe. It functions as both an Ethernet network adapter for broadband Internet, and a modem for dial-up.</p><p>In North America, the adapter launched with several <a href=\"/online/3015-559/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-559\">online-capable</a> games: <a href=\"/socom-us-navy-seals/3030-6246/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-6246\">SOCOM: U.S. Navy SEALs</a>, <a href=\"/nfl-gameday-2003/3030-16405/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-16405\">NFL GameDay 2003</a>, <a href=\"/madden-nfl-2003/3030-15987/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-15987\">Madden NFL 2003</a>, <a href=\"/nfl-2k3/3030-10530/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-10530\">NFL 2K3</a>, and <a href=\"/twisted-metal-black-online/3030-9267/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-9267\">Twisted Metal: Black ONLINE</a>, which could be obtained for free using a mail-order coupon that came with the adapter.</p><p>The slimline PS2 does not support the adapter, though later revisions of the system include a built-in Ethernet port. No slimline PS2s support the HDD, however, which prevents users from playing online games like <a href=\"/final-fantasy-xi-online/3030-11142/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-11142\">Final Fantasy XI</a> that require a hard drive.</p>',0,NULL,0),
(70,68,'2014-03-09 05:43:05','2014-03-09 06:06:48','MOGA Ace Power',NULL,'MOGA Ace Power IOS Controller.','','','<h2> Game Compatibility</h2><ul><li>Budgom 2</li><li><a href=\"/limbo/3030-30380/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-30380\">Limbo</a></li><li><a href=\"/dead-trigger-2/3030-44456/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-44456\">Dead Trigger 2</a></li><li><a href=\"/galaxy-on-fire-2/3030-33507/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-33507\">Galaxi on Fire 2 HD</a></li><li><a href=\"/oceanhorn-monster-of-uncharted-seas/3030-43255/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-43255\">Oceanhorn</a></li><li><a href=\"/bastion/3030-32085/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-32085\">Bastion</a></li><li><a href=\"/fur-fighters/3030-570/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-570\">FurFighters</a></li><li><a href=\"/otto-matic/3030-28872/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-28872\">Otto Matic</a></li></ul>',0,NULL,0),
(71,69,'2014-03-18 18:32:54','2016-10-23 04:43:45','PlayStation VR',NULL,'PlayStation VR, formerly known as Project Morpheus, is a virtual reality headset developed by Sony for the PlayStation 4.','','','<h2>Overview</h2><p>A <a href=\"/head-tracking/3015-606/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-606\">head-tracking</a> <a href=\"/virtual-reality/3015-421/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-421\">virtual reality</a> headset developed by <a href=\"/sony-corporation/3010-3223/\" data-ref-id=\"3010-3223\">Sony</a> for the <a href=\"/playstation-4/3045-146/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-146\">PlayStation 4</a>, released on October 13th 2016. It is similar to the <a href=\"/oculus-rift/3000-41/\" data-ref-id=\"3000-41\">Oculus Rift</a>, <a href=\"/htc-vive/3000-84/\" data-ref-id=\"3000-84\">HTC Vive</a>.</p><p>For a full list of games that are compatible go to the <a href=\"/playstation-vr-support/3015-8700/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-8700\">PlayStation VR Support concept page</a>.</p><h2>History</h2><p>Morpheus marks PlayStation\'s second venture into virtual reality, the first one being the PUD-J5A headset for the <a href=\"/playstation-2/3045-19/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-19\">PlayStation 2</a> which was released in Japan in 2002.</p><h2>Hardware</h2><p>At the <a href=\"/game-developers-conference/3015-6699/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-6699\">Games Developers Conference 2015</a>, Sony unveiled a prototype codenamed Morpheus. Features included the display having an OLED 1920 x 1080 pixel display and capable of displaying content at 120fps, a field of view of 100°, stereoscopic 3D, six degrees of freedom head-tracking and unwarped output to a TV which would show what the headset sees or a separate display to compete against the headset wearer in certain games.</p><p>Later on it was revealed there would be three rendering modes, two being native at 90 Hz and 120 Hz, another is 60 Hz that would be displayed at 120 Hz using asynchronous reprojection. Asynchronous Reprojection is a motion interpolation technique which can achieve a small latency of under 18 milliseconds with little system resources.</p><p>In the final shipping box of PlayStation VR was the headset, a processing unit, VR headset connection cable, HDMI cable, USB cable, stereo headphones, power cord and adapter.</p><h2>Launch Lineup</h2><p>When launched the PlayStation VR came with a demo which had different games which varied by country. This lineup includes standalone games (e.g. Headmaster) and games that had already been released and updated or had extra content created specifically for VR.</p><ul><li><a href=\"/100ft-robot-golf/3030-51745/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-51745\">100ft Robot Golf</a> - No Goblin</li><li><a href=\"/ace-banana/3030-56773/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-56773\">Ace Banana</a> - Oasis Games</li><li><a href=\"/battlezone/3030-49976/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-49976\">Battlezone</a> - Rebellion</li><li><a href=\"/batman-arkham-vr/3030-54242/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-54242\">Batman: Arkham VR</a> - Warner Bros. Interactive Entertainment</li><li><a href=\"/bound/3030-51735/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-51735\">Bound</a> - Plastic</li><li><a href=\"/driveclub/3030-41693/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-41693\">Driveclub VR</a> - Evolution Studio</li><li><a href=\"/eve-valkyrie/3030-43609/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-43609\">EVE: Valkyrie</a> - CCP Games</li><li><a href=\"/harmonix-music-vr/3030-54013/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-54013\">Harmonix Music VR</a> - Harmonix Music Systems</li><li><a href=\"/hatsune-miku-project-diva-x/3030-50706/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-50706\">Hatsune Miku: Project DIVA X</a> - SEGA</li><li><a href=\"/headmaster/3030-49978/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-49978\">Headmaster</a> - Frame</li><li><a href=\"/here-they-lie/3030-54244/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-54244\">Here They Lie</a> - Tangentlemen</li><li><a href=\"/hustle-kings/3030-26871/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-26871\">Hustle Kings VR</a> - EPOS Game Studios</li><li><a href=\"/job-simulator-the-2050-archives/3030-51766/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-51766\">Job Simulator</a> - Owlchemy Labs</li><li><a href=\"/keep-talking-and-nobody-explodes/3030-47445/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-47445\">Keep Talking and Nobody Explodes</a> - Steel Crate Games</li><li>Loading Human - Maximum Games</li><li>Sports Bar VR - Cherry Pop Games</li><li><a href=\"/super-stardust-ultra/3030-48759/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-48759\">Super Stardust VR</a> - D3T</li><li><a href=\"/playstation-vr-worlds/3030-53044/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-53044\">PlayStation VR Worlds</a> - London Studio</li><li><a href=\"/resident-evil-7-biohazard/3030-54231/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-54231\">Resident Evil 7 Kitchen demo</a> - Capcom</li><li><a href=\"/rez-infinite/3030-51742/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-51742\">Rez Infinite</a> - Enhance Games</li><li><a href=\"/rigs-mechanized-combat-league/3030-49979/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-49979\">RIGS Mechanized Combat League</a> - Guerrilla Cambridge</li><li><a href=\"/rise-of-the-tomb-raider/3030-46549/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-46549\">Rise Of The Tomb Raider</a> - Crystal Dynamics</li><li><a href=\"/superhypercube/3030-25298/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-25298\">Superhypercube</a> - Kokoromi</li><li><a href=\"/the-assembly/3030-46608/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-46608\">The Assembly</a> - nDreams</li><li><a href=\"/the-playroom-vr/3030-53043/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-53043\">The Playroom VR</a> - Japan Studio</li><li><a href=\"/thumper/3030-44425/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-44425\">Thumper</a> - Drool</li><li><a href=\"/tumble-vr/3030-53045/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-53045\">Tumble VR</a> - Supermassive Games</li><li><a href=\"/until-dawn-rush-of-blood/3030-51355/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-51355\">Until Dawn: Rush of Blood</a> - Supermassive Games</li><li><a href=\"/volume/3030-43501/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-43501\">Volume: Coda</a> - Bithell Games</li><li><a href=\"/wayward-sky/3030-49990/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-49990\">Wayward Sky</a> - Uber Entertainment</li><li><a href=\"/world-war-toons/3030-49466/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-49466\">World War Toons</a> - Reload Studios</li><li>Waddle Home - Archiact Interactive</li></ul>',0,NULL,0),
(72,70,'2014-04-19 19:49:05','2014-04-19 20:21:42','OUYA Controller',NULL,'The primary input device for the OUYA video game console.','','','<p>The OUYA controller has a number of features:</p><ul><li>Two thumbsticks</li><li>Raised cross D-Pad</li><li>Four face buttons (O, U, Y, and A)</li><li>Center touchpad</li><li>Four triggers: two left, and two right</li><li>Ⓤ Menu/Pause button</li><li>Wireless Bluetooth connectivity</li><li>Swappable faceplates</li></ul>',0,NULL,0),
(73,71,'2014-04-22 12:35:00','2014-04-22 12:35:00','Amazon Fire Game Controller',NULL,'Wireless blue-tooth controller usable with the Amazon Fire TV.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(74,72,'2014-10-07 13:29:27','2017-01-19 17:21:27','GameCube Controller Adapter',NULL,'The GameCube Controller Adapter is an official adapter for Wii U that connects to the console via USB to support the usage of GameCube Controllers on the console.','','','<p>The device features four <a href=\"/gamecube-controller/3000-47/\" data-ref-id=\"3000-47\">GameCube Controller</a> ports on the front and is connected to the Wii or Wii U console with two USB cables. The black USB serves to power the adapter and transfer data, and the grey USB is used for rumble. <a href=\"/wavebird/3000-37/\" data-ref-id=\"3000-37\">Wavebird </a>controllers can be used with this adapter, too. The adapter is available bundled with Super Smash Bros. for Wii U both either with just the adapter and the game but also with a copy of the game, the adapter and a black Smash-branded GameCube Controller. The adapter can also be purchased separately for £17.99/€19.99/$19.99.</p><p>An initial listing on the official Nintendo UK web-store mentioned that the device works on Wii and can be used for games supporting the Wii Classic Controller line and the Wii U Pro Controller but this seems to have been a mistake since it has been swiftly removed from the item description.</p>',0,NULL,0),
(75,73,'2014-11-02 18:04:08','2014-11-02 18:04:08','Arkanoid Contoller',NULL,'An NES paddle controller packaged with Arkanoid. Consisted simply of a button, a spinner and an adjustment screw. Also worked with Arkanoid: Revenge of Doh and Super Chase H.Q.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(76,74,'2014-11-02 18:04:46','2015-02-14 16:36:47','SegaScope 3-D Glasses',NULL,'3-D Glasses made for the Sega Master System. Compatible with 8 games including Space Harrier 3D and Outrun 3D.','','','<h2>Overview</h2><p>Released in 1987 for the <a href=\"/sega-master-system/3045-8/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-8\">Sega Master System</a>, these <a href=\"/3-d-glasses/3055-1919/\" data-ref-id=\"3055-1919\">3D glasses</a> use a shutter system to give a <a href=\"/stereoscopic-3d/3015-1204/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-1204\">3D effect</a>. The shutter system allows for full color, but forces the frame rate to run at 50% (usually 30 frames per second). The glasses are only compatible with the first iteration of the Master System, because they hook up to the card port which is not present in later versions of the system.</p><p>In <a href=\"/japan/3035-37/\" data-ref-id=\"3035-37\">Japan</a>, the glasses came bundled with <a href=\"/zaxxon-3-d/3030-1728/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-1728\">Zaxxon 3D</a>.</p><h2>Compatible Games</h2><ul><li><a href=\"/blade-eagle-3-d/3030-18151/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-18151\">Blade Eagle 3D</a></li><li><a href=\"/maze-hunter-3-d/3030-11858/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-11858\">Maze Hunter 3D</a></li><li><a href=\"/missile-defense-3-d/3030-19870/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-19870\">Missile Defense 3D</a></li><li><a href=\"/outrun/3030-11260/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-11260\">Outrun 3D</a></li><li><a href=\"/poseidon-wars-3-d/3030-20312/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-20312\">Poseidon Wars 3D</a></li><li><a href=\"/space-harrier-3-d/3030-10291/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-10291\">Space Harrier 3D</a></li><li><a href=\"/zaxxon-3-d/3030-1728/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-1728\">Zaxxon 3D</a></li><li><a href=\"/line-of-fire/3030-3688/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-3688\">Line of Fire</a></li></ul><h2>See Also</h2><ul><li><a href=\"/power-base-converter/3000-23/\" data-ref-id=\"3000-23\">Power Base Converter</a></li><li><a href=\"/sega-vr/3000-17/\" data-ref-id=\"3000-17\">Sega VR</a></li><li><a href=\"/x-e-1-a-p/3000-80/\" data-ref-id=\"3000-80\">XE-1AP</a></li><li><a href=\"/sega-activator/3000-8/\" data-ref-id=\"3000-8\">Sega Activator</a></li></ul><p> </p>',0,NULL,0),
(77,75,'2014-11-02 18:08:54','2014-11-02 18:08:55','U-Force',NULL,'An NES controller made by Brøderbund. It used IR sensors to control on screen action, rather than buttons.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(78,76,'2014-11-02 18:13:36','2014-11-02 18:13:37','Roll & Rocker',NULL,'An NES controller where a player stood on a board and shifted his/her weight in order to control the directional pad.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(79,77,'2014-11-02 18:14:54','2015-03-31 15:15:01','NES Speed Board',NULL,'An NES accessory that was designed to hold a controller so the user didn\'t have to. Released in 1991, the idea was that it would allow the player to press buttons faster.  It was poorly received and production was halted shortly after its release.','','','<blockquote><p> </p></blockquote>',0,NULL,0),
(80,78,'2015-01-27 14:47:34','2015-04-19 06:49:44','XE-1AP',NULL,'The XE-1AP, or XE-1 AP, is a controller released by Dempa Micomsoft in 1989, only for Japan, originally for the Sega Mega Drive (Genesis) console. Ahead of its time, it was the first controller to feature an analogue thumbstick, analog slider, shoulder buttons and grip handles.','','','<h2>Overview</h2><figure data-align=\"right\" data-size=\"medium\" data-img-src=\"https://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/original/13/139866/2743364-0996189674-20090.jpg\" data-ref-id=\"1300-2743364\" data-ratio=\"0.75\" data-width=\"800\" data-embed-type=\"image\" style=\"width: 800px\"><a class=\"fluid-height\" style=\"padding-bottom:75.0%\" href=\"https://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/original/13/139866/2743364-0996189674-20090.jpg\" data-ref-id=\"1300-2743364\"><img alt=\"XE-1AP\" src=\"https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/13/139866/2743364-0996189674-20090.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/original/13/139866/2743364-0996189674-20090.jpg 800w, https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/scale_medium/13/139866/2743364-0996189674-20090.jpg 480w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 480px) 100vw, 480px\" data-width=\"480\"></a><figcaption>XE-1AP</figcaption></figure><p>Originally released by <a href=\"/dempa-micomsoft/3010-4743/\" data-ref-id=\"3010-4743\">Dempa Micomsoft</a> for the <a href=\"/genesis/3045-6/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-6\">Sega Mega Drive</a> (Genesis) console in 1989, this analogue controller has the following features:</p><ul><li>Six face buttons</li><li>Four shoulder buttons</li><li>Analogue thumbstick</li><li>Analogue slider, for a third axis or throttle, which can be rotated to suit the user</li><li>Two grip handles, at the bottom, to grip the controller</li><li>Four switches</li></ul><p>The controller was an attempt at simulating/miniaturizing the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HOTAS\" rel=\"nofollow \">HOTAS</a> controls of arcade cabinets such as <a href=\"/sega/3010-62/\" data-ref-id=\"3010-62\">Sega</a>\'s <a href=\"/after-burner-ii/3030-2139/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-2139\">After Burner II</a> on a handheld controller for home systems.</p><h2>Compatibility</h2><h3>Hardware</h3><p>While it was originally created for the <a href=\"/genesis/3045-6/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-6\">Sega Mega Drive (Genesis)</a> console, it was also compatible with various other Japanese systems.</p><p>The XE-1AP was compatible with the following systems:</p><p>Consoles:</p><ul><li><a href=\"/genesis/3045-6/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-6\">Sega Mega Drive (Genesis)</a></li><li><a href=\"/sega-cd/3045-29/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-29\">Sega Mega CD (Sega CD)</a></li><li><a href=\"/sega-32x/3045-31/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-31\">Sega Super 32X (Sega 32X / Mega 32X)</a></li><li><a href=\"/turbografx-16/3045-55/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-55\">PC Engine (TurboGrafx-16)</a></li><li><a href=\"/fm-towns/3045-108/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-108\">FM Towns Marty</a></li></ul><p><a href=\"/pc/3045-94/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-94\">Computers</a>:</p><ul><li><a href=\"/msx/3045-15/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-15\">MSX</a></li><li><a href=\"/nec-pc-8801/3045-109/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-109\">NEC PC-88</a></li><li><a href=\"/sharp-x68000/3045-95/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-95\">Sharp 68000</a></li><li><a href=\"/fm-towns/3045-108/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-108\">Fujitsu FM Towns</a></li></ul><h3>Software</h3><p>The XE-1AP was compatible with the following games on Sega consoles:</p><p><a href=\"/genesis/3045-6/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-6\">Sega Mega Drive (Genesis)</a></p><ul><li><a href=\"/after-burner-ii/3030-2139/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-2139\">After Burner II</a> (1990)</li><li><a href=\"/ayrton-sennas-super-monaco-gp-ii/3030-8935/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-8935\">Ayrton Senna\'s Super Monaco GP II</a> (1992)</li><li>Fastest 1 (1991)</li><li><a href=\"/galaxy-force-ii/3030-8320/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-8320\">Galaxy Force II</a> (1991)</li><li><a href=\"/musha/3030-7928/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-7928\">Musha Aleste</a> (1990)</li></ul><p><a href=\"/sega-cd/3045-29/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-29\">Sega Mega CD (Sega CD)</a></p><ul><li><a href=\"/after-burner-iii/3030-3845/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-3845\">After Burner III</a> (1992)</li><li>Night Striker (1993)</li><li><a href=\"/starblade/3030-1716/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-1716\">Starblade</a> (1994)</li></ul><p><a href=\"/sega-32x/3045-31/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-31\">Sega Super 32X (Sega 32X / Mega 32X)</a></p><ul><li><a href=\"/after-burner/3030-3629/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-3629\">After Burner Complete</a> (1995)</li><li><a href=\"/space-harrier/3030-6036/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-6036\">Space Harrier</a> (1994)</li></ul><h2>Legacy</h2><p>Released in 1989, its use of shoulder buttons predates the release of the <a href=\"/super-nintendo-entertainment-system/3045-9/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-9\">SNES</a> controller in 1990. Its use of grip handles and four shoulder buttons also predates the <a href=\"/playstation/3045-22/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-22\">PlayStation</a> controller\'s 1994 release by five years. Its use of an analogue thumbstick also predates the <a href=\"/nintendo-64/3045-43/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-43\">Nintendo 64</a> controller\'s 1995 announcement by six years and its 1996 release by seven years. Its additional analog slider was also a precursor to the <a href=\"/twin-stick-control/3015-3933/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-3933\">second analog stick</a> of the PlayStation\'s <a href=\"/dualshock-controller/3000-1/\" data-ref-id=\"3000-1\">Dual Shock</a> controller in 1997.</p><p>The XE-1AP is similar in design to the <a href=\"/saturn/3045-42/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-42\">Sega Saturn</a>\'s 3D Control Pad, released in 1996. In turn, the Saturn\'s 3D Control Pad was the basis for the 1998 <a href=\"/dreamcast/3045-37/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-37\">Dreamcast</a> controller, which in turn was the basis for the 2001 <a href=\"/xbox/3045-32/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-32\">Xbox</a> controller, in turn the basis for the 2005 <a href=\"/xbox-360-controller/3000-44/\" data-ref-id=\"3000-44\">Xbox 360 Controller</a>.</p><h2>References</h2><ul><li><a href=\"http://www.gamepilgrimage.com/content/micomsofts-xe-1ap-analogue-controller\" rel=\"nofollow \" data-ref-id=\"false\">Micomsoft\'s XE-1AP Analogue Controller</a></li><li><a href=\"http://segaretro.org/XE-1_AP\" rel=\"nofollow \" data-ref-id=\"false\">XE-1 AP</a></li></ul><h2>See Also</h2><ul><li><a href=\"/sega-vr/3000-17/\" data-ref-id=\"3000-17\">Sega VR</a></li><li><a href=\"/sega-activator/3000-8/\" data-ref-id=\"3000-8\">Sega Activator</a></li><li><a href=\"/segascope-3-d-glasses/3000-76/\" data-ref-id=\"3000-76\">SegaScope 3-D Glasses</a></li></ul><p> </p>',0,NULL,0),
(81,79,'2015-04-20 18:38:11','2018-06-15 21:04:54','Game Boy Player',NULL,'A hardware accessory that attached to the bottom of the GameCube through its high-speed parallel port. This allowed Game Boy, Game Boy Color, or Game Boy Advance games to be played on a TV with GameCube controllers or a GBA. Also required was the included Game Boy Player Startup disc that went in the GameCube\'s disc drive.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(82,80,'2015-05-10 11:26:28','2015-05-10 11:26:29','Sufami Turbo',NULL,'A cartridge with two cartridge ports on it, Bandai\'s Sufami Turbo gave the developer cheaper ways to produce and release a small handful of Super Famicom games.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(83,81,'2015-06-13 14:27:13','2015-06-13 15:06:50','Shooting Gallery',NULL,'Magnavox\'s light gun accessory to it\'s Odyssey video game console. Released in 1972, \"Shooting Gallery\" made its mark on history not only as the first light gun for consoles, but also as Nintendo\'s first involvement in the video game industry.','','','<h4>Game Pack</h4><p>Shooting Gallery shipped with four games that utilized the light gun accessory, stored on two cartridges (#9 and #10). Like other games for the <a href=\"/odyssey/3045-74/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-74\" data-mce-href=\"/odyssey/3045-74/\">Odyssey</a> console, they were colorized by placing a translucent plastic screen overlay on the TV.</p><ul><li><em>Dogfight</em></li><li><em>Prehistoric Safari</em></li><li><em>Shooting Gallery</em></li><li><em>Shootout</em></li></ul><h4>Commercial Performance</h4><p>When released, a false rumor circulated that <em>Shooting Gallery</em> would only work on <a href=\"/magnavox/3010-1164/\" data-ref-id=\"3010-1164\" data-mce-href=\"/magnavox/3010-1164/\">Magnavox</a>-made TV set, hurting sales. There was also a \"bug\" in the light gun system. The rifle would only detect light itself and no particular target, meaning that the player could shoot at any light source, such as a light bulb, and the gun would register it as a hit on a target onscreen.</p><p>Coupled with a $25 price tag, <em>Shooting Gallery</em> experienced very limited commercial success, selling only around 20,000 units.</p>',0,NULL,0),
(84,82,'2015-06-21 16:04:38','2016-06-25 20:20:42','HTC Vive',NULL,'The HTC Vive is a virtual reality headset for the PC, developed in co-production between Valve and HTC.','','','<p>The consumer version of the Vive shipped out in June of 2016.</p><p>The Vive supports 3 main types of experiences: <a href=\"/seated-vr/3015-8786/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-8786\">Seated</a>, <a href=\"/standing-vr/3015-8787/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-8787\">Standing</a>, and <a href=\"/roomscale/3015-8785/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-8785\">Roomscale</a>.</p><p><a href=\"/seated-vr/3015-8786/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-8786\">Seated </a>and <a href=\"/standing-vr/3015-8787/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-8787\">Standing </a>are as they sound and require little elaboration.</p><p><a href=\"/roomscale/3015-8785/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-8785\">Roomscale </a>requires a space of a minimum of 1m by 1m, extending up to 3m by 3m. The room needs to have the \"VR Lighthouses\" installed, and then to be configured by pacing it out with the controllers. A caveat of this is that mirrors will interfere with the invisible beams that are used for lay out the space, confusing the system.</p><p>Before purchasing the Vive, running the Steam VR Performance test is recommended, to confirm that system will be able to handle the graphical requirements.</p>',0,NULL,0),
(85,83,'2015-06-25 16:55:31','2015-06-26 18:29:30','Oculus Touch',NULL,'Oculus Touch is the name of Oculus\' motion-tracking controllers for use with its Rift VR headset.','','','<p>The Oculus Touch controllers were unveiled as part of the company\'s pre-E3 press conference for 2015. The controllers are specifically referred to as the \"Half Moon Prototype.\"</p>',0,NULL,0),
(86,84,'2015-06-25 17:01:58','2015-07-29 19:15:56','Microsoft HoloLens',NULL,'HoloLens is a wireless set of augmented reality goggles developed by Microsoft.','','','<h2>Overview</h2><p>Microsoft Hololens is a mixed reality head mounted display that runs on a new computing platform called Windows Holographic.</p><h2>Technology</h2><p>Built into Hololens is a depth camera with a 120°×120° angle of view, a microphone array, and a photographic video camera. The unit also includes an accelerometer, gyroscope, and a magnetometer.</p><p> </p><p>The unit also has built in stereo speakers that do not block the users ability to hear the real world environment.</p><p> </p><h2>Games Supported</h2><p>Currently, the only game that has been officially announced for Hololens is <a href=\"/minecraft/3030-30475/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-30475\">Minecraft</a>. At <a href=\"/e3-2015/3015-8442/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-8442\">E3 2015</a>, Microsoft showed off a prototype demo off first person shooter called Project X-ray.</p>',0,NULL,0),
(87,85,'2015-08-12 19:30:31','2015-09-19 01:27:34','Xbox Elite Wireless Controller',NULL,'Microsoft\'s pro-level controller featuring interchangeable back paddles, D-pad and thumbsticks, as well as hair trigger locks. The controller will allow for button-mapping using a custom-made app on both Xbox One and Windows 10.','','','<p> </p>',0,NULL,0),
(88,86,'2015-09-07 17:11:43','2015-09-07 23:43:25','Atari Paddle Controllers',NULL,'Spinner controllers packed in with the Atari VCS/2600 game console','','','<p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\">The Atari paddle controllers are analog spinner game controllers for the <a href=\"/atari-2600/3045-40/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-40\">Atari VCS/2600</a> console. Paddles were manufactured in pairs, and two controllers plug into a single input, resulting in up to four-player multiplayer (with two paddle pairs). Additionally, each controller has a side-mounted button. While the original version shipped in 1977 with the Atari VCS, an updated version was released in 1978 with minor differences in the sticker graphics, and is somewhat shorter overall. Over 50 games were designed to use the paddle controller over the life of the system.</p><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\">Like the <a href=\"/atari-vcs-joystick/3055-785/\" data-ref-id=\"3055-785\">Atari joystick</a>, paddles are compatible with certain other consoles which use the same input scheme. One notable example is <a href=\"/super-breakout/3030-1055/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-1055\">Super Breakout</a> for the <a href=\"/atari-8-bit/3045-24/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-24\">Atari 800</a>, which has 4 inputs, allowing up to 8-player simultaneous play.</p><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\">The similar Atari <a href=\"/atari-driving-controller/3000-89/\" data-ref-id=\"3000-89\">driving controller</a> was released in 1977, but is officially only supported by <a href=\"/indy-500/3030-19945/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-19945\">Indy 500</a>.</p>',0,NULL,0),
(89,87,'2015-09-07 17:30:34','2015-09-07 17:44:30','Atari Driving Controller',NULL,'Similar to the Atari paddle, only Indy 500 officially supports this controller','','','<p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\">The Atari driving controller is the pack-in controller for <a href=\"/indy-500/3030-19945/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-19945\">Indy 500</a>. Though similar in appearance to the <a href=\"/atari-paddle-controllers/3000-88/\" data-ref-id=\"3000-88\">paddle controller</a>, the driving controller\'s spinner can be rotated infinitely (the paddle has a hard lock after a complete spin, and rebounds to center). The driving controller is only supported by the single game, but like the paddle, underwent a minor re-design in 1978, a year after release.</p><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\">The driving controller was packed in pairs with Indy 500, but each controller has its own input, allowing only two-player simultaneous play (compared to the paddles\' four). Though the controller is generically branded for driving games, other driving games (such as <a href=\"/night-driver/3030-13617/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-13617\">Night Driver</a>) use the paddle or <a href=\"/atari-vcs-joystick/3055-785/\" data-ref-id=\"3055-785\">joystick</a>, not the driving controller.</p>',0,NULL,0),
(91,88,'2015-09-07 21:58:19','2015-09-07 22:54:06','Atari Keypad',NULL,'Keypad controller for the Atari 2600','','','<p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\">A limited number of Atari 2600 games (and <a href=\"/basic-programming/3030-23772/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-23772\">Basic Programming</a>) use these keypads for input. They were sold separately in pairs, with an overlay for Basic Programming. The standard version features a slide-lock mechanism to connect two controllers together, for a single, extra wide keypad. Several functionally identical controllers were produced. Star Raiders was packed with the Video Touch Pad, and a game-specific overlay. The Kid\'s Controller was a larger, blue-colored version.</p><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\">Compatible titles include:</p><ul><li><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\">Basic Programming</p></li><li><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"> </p><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"><a href=\"/brain-games/3030-6172/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-6172\">Brain Games</a></p></li><li><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"> </p><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"><a href=\"/codebreaker/3030-12823/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-12823\">Codebreaker</a></p></li><li><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"> </p><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"><a href=\"/a-game-of-concentration/3030-25476/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-25476\">Game of Concentration</a></p></li><li><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"> </p><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"><a href=\"/hunt-score/3030-12374/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-12374\">Hunt &amp; Score</a></p></li><li><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"> </p><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"><a href=\"/videocart-15-memory-match/3030-26672/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-26672\">Memory Match</a></p></li><li><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\">Testcart</p></li><li><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"> </p><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"><a href=\"/alpha-beam-with-ernie/3030-15182/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-15182\">Alpha Beam with Ernie</a></p></li><li><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"> </p><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"><a href=\"/big-birds-egg-catch/3030-11230/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-11230\">Big Bird\'s Egg Catch</a></p></li><li><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"><a href=\"/cookie-monster-munch/3030-3151/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-3151\">Cookie Monster Munch</a></p></li><li><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"> </p><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\">Grover\'s Music Maker</p></li><li><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\">Monstercise</p></li><li><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"> </p><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"><a href=\"/oscars-trash-race/3030-20086/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-20086\"> Oscar\'s Trash Race</a></p></li><li><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"> </p><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\">Peek-a-Boo</p></li><li><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"> </p><p data-right-indent=\"0\" data-left-indent=\"0\"><a href=\"/star-raiders/3030-730/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-730\">Star Raiders</a></p></li></ul>',0,NULL,0),
(93,89,'2015-09-10 08:27:10','2015-09-10 08:29:31','Atari Track & Field Controller',NULL,'Included with the Atari 2600 Track &amp; Field port','','','<p>The Atari 2600 release of <a href=\"/track-field/3030-18232/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-18232\">Track &amp; Field</a> included this controller to mimic the Arcade\'s button mashing input. The controller buttons are simply mapped to the joystick \"left\", \"right\", and \"fire\". The controller was also sold separately for use on systems with compatible inputs.</p>',0,NULL,0),
(94,90,'2015-10-09 02:05:44','2015-10-09 02:06:26','Rock Revolution Drum Set',NULL,'The drums for Rock Revolution','','','',0,NULL,0),
(95,91,'2015-10-23 20:38:03','2015-10-23 20:38:03','Steam Controller',NULL,'A highly configurable controller designed for the PC by Valve. It features dual touch pads with haptic feedback, dual-stage triggers, dual grip buttons, vibration, and gyroscopic motion controls.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(96,92,'2016-02-25 14:47:11','2021-12-21 15:06:40','OSVR Hacker Development Kit',NULL,'Open Source Virtual Reality Headmounted Display','','','<h2>Overview</h2><p>Open Source Virtual Reality (OSVR) is a virtual reality head-up display project that is an open hardware device and uses open source software.</p><p>OSVR consists of two main and independent parts: open source schematics and drawings and open source software.</p><p>Open source software enables VR developers to discover, configure, and control VR devices across a wide range of operating systems. This software is licensed under Apache 2.0.</p><p>The main sponsors of the project are <a href=\"https://www.razer.com/\" data-target=\"true\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Razer Inc.</a> and Sensics.</p><p>The HDK1 Self-Build Kit, version 1.4, was available to order in 2017 from the developer and enthusiast on the <a href=\"https://www2.razer.com/vr/hdk1/\" data-target=\"true\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">project website</a>.</p>',0,NULL,0),
(97,93,'2016-05-22 09:15:21','2016-05-22 09:15:21','Razer Serval',NULL,'The Serval from Razer is a Bluetooth Android controller. It was specifically designed for their Forge TV console, but is compatible with most, if not all, Android devices.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(98,94,'2016-06-26 05:11:01','2016-06-30 17:38:17','VR Lighthouse',NULL,'The device that allows for Vive\'s Roomscale.','','','<p> These devices broadcast an IR grid that is seen by the cameras located on the other Vive accessories. They have 3 channels they can be set for: A, for single Lighthouse usage, which does not support roomscale and channels B &amp; C are used to create Roomscale, being positioned in opposite corners.</p><p>The Lighthouses have screwplates on the back and bottom, and include a mounting plate. They can also be used with standard camera tripods. </p>',0,NULL,0),
(100,95,'2017-01-18 18:16:31','2017-02-05 00:54:25','Dreamcast Twin Stick',NULL,'A Dreamcast peripheral controller designed for use with Cyber Troopers Virtual-On: Oratorio Tangram.','','','<p>Released 12/09/1999 only in Japan, the Dreamcast Twinstick is a 4 button, 2 trigger, dual stick controller. The controller was made specifically for use with the dreamcast release of Virtual-On: Oratorio Tangram.</p><p>The dimensions of the controller are: 2.25\" tall, 11\" wide, and 8\" deep. There is a slight slant to the top of the controller starting at 1.75\", from the player facing side of controller, to the top of the controller. While the top of the controller is plastic the bottom of the controller is metal with 6 black foam circular pads to prevent sliding. There are 18 screw holes on the controller and 16 screws (two screws go through both 2 holes each) holding it together, 6 screw holes on the right stick, 6 on the left stick, and six on the bottom of the controller.</p><p>The controller has 1 VMU port at the top of the controller, below this is a 75\" wire allowing the console to connect to the dreamcast controller port. Each joystick on the controller has one button on top to be pressed by the player\'s thumb and one on the front to be pressed by the player\'s index finger.</p><p>The only model number sold of this controller is: HKT-7500</p><h2>Compatible Games</h2><ul><li>Virtual-On: Oratorio Tangram</li><li>OutTrigger</li><li>Quake III Arena</li><li>Rez</li><li>Ikaruga</li><li>Soulcalibur</li><li>Virtua Tennis</li></ul>',0,NULL,0),
(101,96,'2017-05-02 21:36:30','2023-04-03 17:56:06','Joy-Con',NULL,'Joy-Con is the primary input device for the Nintendo Switch.','','','<p>The Nintendo Switch ships with two Joy-Con, along with a wrist strap for each. They can be used and charged while attached to the Nintendo Switch console via rails, or they can be used while detached. Detaching the Joy-Con allows them to be used in other accessories, or they can be used for two-player.</p><p> </p><h2>Features</h2><p>Each Joy-Con has an analog stick, four digital direction buttons, a - or + button, and three \'shoulder\' buttons, one on top of the controller and two more on the rail. The left Joy-Con has a capture button, while the right Joy-Con has a Home button.</p><p>Joy-Con have HD Rumble, which allows them to vibrate to create precise sensations, such as balls rolling in a box. </p><figure data-align=\"right\" data-size=\"small\" data-img-src=\"https://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/original/16/164924/2935953-joycon.png\" data-ref-id=\"1300-2935953\" data-ratio=\"0.94583333333333\" data-width=\"1200\" data-embed-type=\"image\" style=\"width: 1200px\"><a class=\"fluid-height\" style=\"padding-bottom:94.6%\" href=\"https://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/original/16/164924/2935953-joycon.png\" data-ref-id=\"1300-2935953\"><img alt=\"No Caption Provided\" src=\"https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/original/16/164924/2935953-joycon.png\" srcset=\"https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/original/16/164924/2935953-joycon.png 0w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px\" data-width=\"320\"></a></figure><p>Each Joy-Con have an accelerometer and gyroscope that can be used for motion tracking. They can allow pointing controls such as the Wii and Wii U had without the need for a sensor bar.</p><p>The right Joy-Con has an infrared depth tracking sensor capable of distinguishing objects and shapes. It also has an NFC reader to use for Amiibo.</p><p>The batteries have a reported life of 20 hours.</p>',0,NULL,0),
(102,97,'2017-12-31 23:06:42','2017-12-31 23:06:42','Game Master',NULL,'A cheat device for the MSX which allowed players to change variables in games that Konami published for the system.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(103,98,'2018-02-16 12:04:21','2024-06-03 18:25:57','Datach Joint Rom System',NULL,'A Japan-only add-on by Bandai for the Famicom that utilizes a barcode scanner for special trading cards. Only seven games were made for it (all of which are first-party and use unique half-sized cartridges).','','','<h2>Games</h2><ul><li><a href=\"/dragon-ball-z-gekitou-tenkaichi-budoukai/3030-66445/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-66445\">Dragon Ball Z: Gekitou Tenkaichi Budoukai</a> (pack-in)</li><li><a href=\"/ultraman-club-spokon-fight/3030-91042/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-91042\">Ultraman Club: Spokon Fight!</a></li><li><a href=\"/sd-gundam-gundam-wars/3030-32203/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-32203\">SD Gundam: Gundam Wars</a></li><li><a href=\"/crayon-shin-chan-orato-to-poi-poi/3030-40038/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-40038\">Crayon Shin-Chan: Orato Poi Poi</a></li><li><a href=\"/yuyu-hakusho-bakutou-ankoku-bujutsu-kai/3030-32334/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-32334\">Yuu Yuu Hakusho: Bakutou Ankoku Bujutsue</a></li><li><a href=\"/battle-rush-build-up-robot-tournament/3030-36500/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-36500\">Battle Rush: Build Up Robot Tournament</a></li><li>J-League Super Top Players</li></ul>',0,NULL,0),
(104,99,'2018-03-24 18:28:02','2018-03-24 18:28:35','Starpath Supercharger',NULL,'A peripheral for the Atari 2600 which expanded the 2600\'s RAM capabilities 49-fold, allowing for much more complex games.','','','<p> For a list of games which utilized this accessory, see <a href=\"/starpath-supercharger/3015-9139/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-9139\">here</a>.</p>',0,NULL,0),
(105,100,'2018-05-14 08:17:23','2018-05-14 08:17:23','Action Replay MAX',NULL,NULL,'','','',0,NULL,0),
(106,101,'2018-05-20 06:32:29','2019-01-13 18:38:34','Xbox Adaptive Controller ',NULL,'A special Xbox One controller designed for gamers with physical disabilities.','','','<p>The Xbox Adaptive Controller is a hub with ports for each regular Xbox controller input, allowing users to configure individual devices to be used to represent the complete array of control functionality however they want. The hub includes 19 3.5mm ports and 2 USB 2.0 ports for external devices. There is also one 3.5mm stereo headset jack for audio. It can be connected to Xbox One consoles and Windows 10 PCs using Bluetooth and USB-C connections.</p>',0,NULL,0),
(107,102,'2018-05-29 15:30:10','2018-06-15 21:03:16','AirStrike',NULL,'The AirStrike drum controller was packed in with Power Gig: Rise of the Six string, a rhythm game for Xbox 360 and PlayStation 3. Rather than having physical pads to drum on, there were four colored sensors that detected when the included drum sticks entered the air space above them. Also included was a bass-drum pedal.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(108,103,'2019-02-21 17:49:36','2019-02-21 17:49:36','PlayStation Analog Joystick',NULL,'The first analog controller released for Sony\'s PS1 released in the United States in 1995 and Japan in 1996. Compatible with over 40 games.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(109,104,'2019-02-21 18:12:26','2019-02-21 18:19:27','PlayStation Dual Analog Controller',NULL,'Sony\'s first analog controller, which predates the DualShock by over a year.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(112,105,'2019-12-17 07:46:14','2020-02-14 20:52:00','DualShock 4 Back Button Attachment',NULL,'An attachment for the Dualshock 4 controller that adds two programmable back buttons.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(113,106,'2020-04-07 13:10:48','2020-04-07 13:15:44','DualSense Controller',NULL,'The DualSense controller is the primary controller for the PlayStation 5.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(114,107,'2021-02-15 15:12:28','2021-02-15 18:11:40','Mega Modem',NULL,'An early Japanese-exclusive dial-up modem accessory for the Sega Mega Drive.','','','<h2>Overview</h2><p>The Mega Modem is a first-party dial-up modem accessory developed by <a href=\"/sega/3010-62/\" data-ref-id=\"3010-62\">Sega</a> for the <a href=\"/genesis/3045-6/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-6\">Sega Mega Drive</a> exclusively in Japan on November 3, 1990. The peripheral was almost sold in North America as the <em>TeleGenesis</em> modem, but this plan was scrapped prior to release.</p><p>One of the few (only?) peripherals to support the 9-pin EXT port of the first-generation Sega Mega Drive, the Mega Modem allowed certain games and software to make dial-up connections through an attached telephone line. The peripheral itself also includes a built-in microphone and speaker for use with some software.</p><p>As the modem was limited to slow 1.2 kbps speed connections, only a handful of games use the peripheral for turn-based communication. In addition, the peripheral was used for other services (all requiring a monthly subscription fee):</p><ul><li>Digital game distribution through the <a href=\"/sega-meganet/3015-7697/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-7697\">Sega Game Toshokan / Sega Game Library</a> software cartridge. With a 800円 monthly fee, players could download small-sized games to the cartridge for play, released between 1990 and 1992. Most of these games were exclusive to the service at the time, with most released later as part of the <a href=\"/game-no-kanzume/3025-3585/\" data-ref-id=\"3025-3585\">Game no Kanzume</a> series and some official emulation services. It also included game soundtracks and an online newsletter.</li></ul><ul><li>Digital home banking using the <em>Mega Anser</em> software cartridge and its bundled Ten Key Pad input peripheral (and optional thermal printer attachment). Specialized versions of the cartridge were made for specific financial institutions: <em>Naisu-kun Mini</em>, <em>Osaka Ginkou no Home Banking Service: My Line</em>, and <em>Sumisei Home Tanmatsu</em>.</li></ul><ul><li>Receiving game statistics, both real-time and post-game, for professional baseball through the <em>Nikkan Sports Pro Yakyuu VAN</em> software cartridge. This utilized a monthly subscription fee and can show a visualized representation of each play as if it was a video game.</li></ul><p>These concepts were later revisited for the Mega Drive using cartridge-based modems, including the <a href=\"/sega-channel/3015-5038/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-5038\">Sega Channel</a> (an official digital game distribution service using coaxial cable connections), the Mega Net (an online multi-use service for Brazil from <a href=\"/tec-toy-industria-de-brinquedos-sa/3010-96/\" data-ref-id=\"3010-96\">Tec Toy</a>, used for e-mail, banking, and chat), and the XBAND (an online multiplayer service from Catapult Entertainment).</p><h2>Supported Games</h2><p>Only seven retail games supported the Mega Modem peripheral:</p><ul><li><a href=\"/advanced-daisenryaku-deutsch-dengeki-sakusen/3030-36902/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-36902\">Advanced Daisenryaku: Deutsch Dengeki Sakusen</a></li><li><a href=\"/cyberball/3030-8655/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-8655\">Cyberball</a></li><li><a href=\"/go-net/3030-81801/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-81801\">GO-NET</a></li><li><a href=\"/shi-kin-joh/3030-36338/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-36338\">Shikinjou</a></li><li>San San: Igo Tsuushin Taikyoku Network</li><li><a href=\"/tel-tel-mahjong/3030-64866/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-64866\">Tel-Tel Mahjong</a></li><li><a href=\"/tel-tel-stadium/3030-69644/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-69644\">Tel-Tel Stadium</a></li></ul><p>As the modem was limited to 1.2 kbps speeds, most games use the peripheral for turn-based multiplayer. Shikinjou uses the service instead for distributing custom stages built with the <a href=\"/in-game-map-editor/3015-269/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-269\">built-in editor</a>.</p><p>Both San San and GO-NET used the peripheral to connect to their own online service, both of which were later discontinued. Both were also the only play-by-mail games for the system, allowing players to continue their games at any time (even picking up the game on their respective <a href=\"/pc/3045-94/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-94\">PC</a> clients).</p>',0,NULL,0),
(115,108,'2021-03-18 05:28:48','2022-11-02 10:36:38','PlayStation VR2',NULL,'Sony\'s second virtual reality device is designed for PlayStation 5. It features new controllers that utilize adaptive triggers and haptic feedback found in the DualSense, but also touch sensitivity for finger tracking.','','','<h2>Overview</h2><p>PlayStation VR2 will be released on February 22, 2023 for $549.99 USD.</p><h3>Headset Specs</h3><ul><li>OLED Display</li><li>2000 x 2040 resolution per eye</li><li>Refresh rate​ 90Hz, 120Hz</li><li>Adjustable lens separation​</li><li>Field of View​ ~110 degrees</li><li>Six-axis motion sensing system (three-axis gyroscope, three-axis accelerometer)​</li><li>IR Proximity sensor</li><li>4 Cameras for Headset and Controller Tracking</li><li>​IR camera for eye tracking per eye</li><li>Feedback​ Vibration on Headset</li><li>Communication​ with PS5 USB Type-C®</li><li>Built-in microphone​</li><li>Stereo headphone jack</li></ul>',0,NULL,0),
(116,109,'2021-04-19 21:57:06','2021-04-19 21:57:57','Comp-K7',NULL,'An expansion cartridge for the Atari 2600, similar to the SuperCharger, in that it allows players to play specially designed cassette tapes in a standard cassette player on the 2600. SuperCharger and Comp-K7 games are not cross-compatible.','','','<h2>Overview</h2><p>The <strong>Comp-K7</strong> was manufactured in Brazil by a company called Splice.</p>',0,NULL,0),
(117,110,'2022-05-14 14:49:30','2022-05-14 14:49:30','Varjo Aero',NULL,'Varjo Aero is one of the most innovative consumer VR headsets for PC developed by Varjo Technologies.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(118,111,'2022-07-31 08:23:54','2022-07-31 08:25:08','TI-99/4A Wired Remote Controller',NULL,'The official controller for the Texas Instruments TI-99/4A Home Computer. ','','','',0,NULL,0),
(119,112,'2022-07-31 08:36:51','2022-07-31 08:37:27','NES Controller',NULL,'The official controller for the Nintendo Entertainment System. ','','','',0,NULL,0),
(120,113,'2022-07-31 08:40:14','2022-07-31 08:43:15','NES Zapper',NULL,'The official light gun accessory for the Nintendo Entertainment System. ','','','',0,NULL,0),
(121,114,'2022-07-31 08:51:53','2022-07-31 08:57:52','Asciiware asciiPad',NULL,'A third-party controller for the SNES that featured turbo and automatic switches for each of the face and shoulder buttons.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(122,115,'2022-07-31 09:04:25','2022-07-31 09:05:53','Asciiware Super Advantage',NULL,'A third-party arcade stick for the Super Nintendo. It features turbo and automatic switches (including speed settings) for all four face buttons and both shoulder buttons. ','','','',0,NULL,0),
(123,116,'2022-07-31 09:31:48','2022-07-31 09:38:28','Super Game Boy',NULL,'The Super Game Boy is an accessory for the Super Nintendo Entertainment System that allows players to play Game Boy games on a television.','','','<h2>Overview</h2><ul><li>Released: June 1994</li><li>Price: $59.99 (US), £49.99 (UK)</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>',0,NULL,0),
(124,117,'2022-07-31 09:46:09','2022-07-31 09:50:02','SN ProgramPad',NULL,'A third-party controller for the Super Nintendo Entertainment System produced by QJ/Interact. It features three programmable buttons that could record inputs with the help of an LCD screen. Primarily used for fighting games.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(125,118,'2022-07-31 10:18:03','2022-07-31 10:32:53','Asciiware Ascii Pad PSS',NULL,'A third-party controller for the Sony PlayStation. It features turbo and automatic switches for all four face buttons and all four shoulder buttons.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(126,119,'2022-07-31 10:47:20','2022-07-31 11:01:32','Asciiware Ascii Grip',NULL,'A third-party controller for the Sony PlayStation that allows players to play games one-handed. Primarily used for role-playing games.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(127,120,'2022-07-31 11:26:28','2022-07-31 11:28:38','PlayStation Controller',NULL,'The original PlayStation controller designed by Sony Computer Entertainment released in December 1994. Model number SCPH-1010.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(128,121,'2022-07-31 11:36:20','2022-07-31 11:39:31','Net Yaroze Controller',NULL,'The official controller designed by Sony Computer Entertainment for use with the Net Yaroze, which is a commercially sold development kit version of the original PlayStation. Model number DTL-H3010, it is charcoal gray in color, which matches the Net Yaroze console.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(129,122,'2022-07-31 12:21:26','2022-07-31 12:30:47','PlayStation Memory Card',NULL,'The official storage device for the original PlayStation. It stored save data in a maximum of fifteen \"blocks\", which were 8KB each.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(130,123,'2022-07-31 12:35:41','2022-07-31 13:00:16','PSone LCD Screen',NULL,'A 5-inch LCD screen designed by Sony Computer Entertainment for the redesigned PlayStation (PSone) in September 2000.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(131,124,'2022-07-31 13:07:31','2022-08-01 18:16:38','Nintendo 64 Controller',NULL,'The official controller designed by Nintendo for use with the Nintendo 64.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(132,125,'2022-07-31 16:11:47','2022-08-01 18:16:31','Nintendo 64 Controller Pak',NULL,'The official storage device designed by Nintendo for use with the Nintendo 64. The original model (NUS-004) holds 32KB of data.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(133,126,'2022-07-31 16:29:16','2022-08-01 18:16:25','Nintendo 64 Jumper Pak',NULL,'The Jumper Pak comes pre-installed in every Nintendo 64 and essentially is a placeholder for the eventual release of the Expansion Pak, which provides more RAM for the console.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(134,127,'2022-07-31 16:35:23','2022-08-01 18:16:17','Nintendo 64 Expansion Pak',NULL,'The Expansion Pak adds 4MB of RAM to the Nintendo 64 console. Originally designed for the 64DD add-on, it is still required for several standard N64 games. In North America, it was packaged with Donkey Kong 64.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(135,128,'2022-07-31 17:00:57','2022-08-01 18:16:10','Nintendo 64 Rumble Pak',NULL,'The Rumble Pak plugs into the back of the Nintendo 64 controller and provides haptic feedback for many of the console\'s games. It is powered by two AAA batteries. ','','','',0,NULL,0),
(136,129,'2022-07-31 17:23:07','2022-07-31 17:24:13','Dreamcast Controller',NULL,'The official controller designed by Sega for the Dreamcast.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(137,130,'2022-07-31 17:42:04','2022-07-31 17:47:37','Dreamcast VMU',NULL,'The Visual Memory Unit (VMU) is the official storage device designed by Sega for the Dreamcast. It features an LCD screen and buttons, which some games utilize as a mini portable gaming system. The screen is also visible while plugged into the controller.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(138,131,'2022-07-31 17:55:08','2022-07-31 17:57:15','Guitar Hero Gibson SG Controller',NULL,'The original Guitar Hero guitar designed by Red Octane.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(139,132,'2022-08-01 14:07:29','2022-08-01 14:09:57','Hori Dragon Quest Slime Controller',NULL,'Originally released for the PlayStation 2 to coincide with Dragon Quest VIII in 2005, Hori\'s slime controller has seen several iterations for other consoles since then.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(140,133,'2022-08-01 14:59:10','2022-08-01 15:04:04','Hori 10th Anniversary Tekken 5 Arcade Stick',NULL,'A limited edition arcade stick released as part of the Ultimate Collector\'s Edition of Tekken 5 for PlayStation 2. Only 20,000 were made.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(141,134,'2022-08-01 15:07:15','2022-08-01 15:08:48','Logitech Cordless Action Controller',NULL,'A third-party controller for the PlayStation 2 and considered by many to be the best wireless option for the console.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(142,135,'2022-08-01 15:22:20','2022-08-01 15:27:22','Logitech Driving Force Pro Force Feedback Wheel',NULL,'The Logitech Driving Force Pro Force Feedback Wheel for the PlayStation 2 was released in 2004 to coincide with the release of Gran Turismo 4. ','','','',0,NULL,0),
(143,136,'2022-08-01 15:38:00','2022-08-01 15:40:52','Namco GunCon 2 Light Gun',NULL,'Namco\'s officially licensed light gun for the PlayStation 2. ','','','',0,NULL,0),
(144,137,'2022-08-01 15:51:45','2022-08-01 19:15:42','PlayStation 2 40GB Hard Drive',NULL,'Released in July 2001 in Japan and March 2004 in North America, the PlayStation 2 Hard Disk Drive is used to enhance certain games\' features such as load times, instant replays, and increased storage.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(145,138,'2022-08-01 16:30:15','2022-08-01 16:33:44','EyeToy',NULL,'Released in 2003, the EyeToy is a camera designed by Richard Marks for the PlayStation 2 that is capable of tracking players\' body movements and offering mixed reality gaming.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(146,139,'2022-08-01 17:22:31','2022-08-01 17:54:37','PlayStation 2 Horizontal Stand',NULL,'Quite possibly the most useless accessory of all time, the Horizontal Stand released by Sony Computer Entertainment for the PlayStation 2 simply adds a blue accent to the front of the console.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(147,140,'2022-08-01 17:29:57','2022-08-01 17:53:48','PlayStation 2 Memory Card',NULL,'The official storage device for PlayStation 2. It offered 8 MB of space for saved games.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(148,141,'2022-08-01 17:58:51','2022-08-01 18:01:37','PlayStation 2 Vertical Stand',NULL,'Released by Sony Computer Entertainment alongside the launch of the PlayStation 2, the Vertical Stand provides stability when placing the console in its upright configuration.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(149,142,'2022-08-01 18:30:59','2022-08-04 08:50:53','GameCube Game Boy Advance Cable',NULL,'This official link cable released by Nintendo in December 2001 allows for various connectivity features between the console and handheld versions of games.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(150,143,'2022-08-01 18:44:33','2022-08-01 18:46:38','Logitech Cordless Precision Controller',NULL,'A third-party controller for the Xbox and considered by many to be the best wireless option for the console.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(151,144,'2022-08-01 19:28:41','2022-08-01 19:33:04','Xbox Controller',NULL,'The original controller designed by Microsoft for use with the Xbox. Becoming known as \"The Duke\", its size was heavily criticized and was replaced a year later.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(152,145,'2022-08-01 19:41:08','2022-08-01 19:42:07','Xbox Controller S',NULL,'Responding to complaints about the size of the original Xbox controller, Microsoft released the Controller S in 2002 and began packaging with all new consoles.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(153,146,'2022-08-02 14:15:56','2022-08-02 14:20:04','GameCube DK Bongos',NULL,'Designed by Namco Bandai, the DK Bongos are an officially licensed controller for the Nintendo GameCube that are primarily used for the Donkey Konga series of rhythm games.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(154,147,'2022-08-02 14:51:33','2022-08-02 14:57:19','GameCube Memory Card',NULL,'The official storage device designed by Nintendo for the GameCube console. The original version (gray) had space for 59 blocks of storage. Two later versions included 251 blocks (black) and 1019 blocks (white). ','','','',0,NULL,0),
(155,148,'2022-08-02 16:05:01','2022-08-02 16:08:04','Memory Stick Duo',NULL,'Designed by Sony for use many of their electronics, the Memory Stick Duo (and Pro Duo) is the official storage device for the PlayStation Portable. Sizes compatible with the PSP range from 32 MB to 128 GB.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(156,149,'2022-08-02 16:14:24','2022-08-02 16:24:31','DJ Hero Turntable Controller',NULL,'Released in 2009 by Activision, it is a unique controller designed specifically for use with the DJ Hero series of games.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(157,150,'2022-08-02 17:26:04','2022-08-02 17:28:53','Guitar Hero Gibson X-plorer Controller',NULL,'Designed by Red Octane, the X-plorer guitar was originally packaged with the Xbox 360 version of Guitar Hero II. ','','','',0,NULL,0),
(158,151,'2022-08-02 17:47:21','2022-08-02 17:53:18','Xbox 360 Hard Drive',NULL,'Released in November 2005, the original model of the Xbox 360 featured an optional, detachable hard drive with a capacity of 20 GB. Later versions of the hard drive included 60 GB, 120 GB, and 250 GB versions.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(159,152,'2022-08-02 17:53:55','2022-08-02 18:00:37','Xbox 360 S Hard Drive',NULL,'In June 2010, Microsoft released a remodeled version of the console known as the Xbox 360 S with a 250 GB hard drive. Special edition versions of the Xbox 360 S included a 320 GB hard drive.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(160,153,'2022-08-03 07:12:47','2022-08-03 07:17:59','Xbox 360 Faceplate',NULL,'The original model of Xbox 360, released in November 2005, featured a removable faceplate. This allowed owners to customize their console.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(161,154,'2022-08-03 07:24:09','2022-08-03 07:29:10','Xbox 360 Hard Drive Transfer Cable',NULL,'The Hard Drive Transfer Cable allows people to transfer their saved data from an original Xbox 360\'s hard drive to an Xbox 360 S or Xbox 360 E hard drive.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(162,155,'2022-08-03 07:36:35','2022-08-03 07:39:32','Xbox 360 Headset',NULL,'The official headset designed by Microsoft for use with Xbox Live on Xbox 360.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(164,156,'2022-08-03 07:54:49','2022-08-03 08:00:35','Xbox 360 Memory Unit',NULL,'The Xbox 360 Memory Unit offers a more portable option for transporting Xbox Live profiles, saved data, and games from one console to another.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(165,157,'2022-08-03 09:51:06','2022-08-03 09:54:08','Xbox 360 Play & Charge Kit',NULL,'The official controller charging device designed by Microsoft for the Xbox 360.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(166,158,'2022-08-03 10:04:58','2022-08-03 10:19:12','Xbox 360 Wireless Networking Adapter',NULL,'The original model of the Xbox 360 did not feature built-in wifi. This official adapter was made available originally in 802.11 A/B/G (white) and then later in 802.11 N (black). ','','','',0,NULL,0),
(167,159,'2022-08-03 10:49:22','2022-08-03 11:09:50','PDP Mortal Kombat Fight Stick',NULL,'PDP\'s Mortal Kombat Fight Stick was released in conjunction with Mortal Kombat (2011) and features the classic X-shaped button layout from the MK arcade games.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(168,160,'2022-08-03 11:24:47','2022-08-03 11:35:30','Rock Band Fender Guitar',NULL,'The official guitar released for the original Rock Band in 2007. While this is a wired version, wireless options were made available later.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(169,161,'2022-08-03 11:42:45','2022-08-03 11:49:56','Rock Band Cymbal Expansion Kit',NULL,'With the release of Rock Band 2, \"Pro\" drums became an option by adding dedicated cymbals to the drum kit. These kits come in single, double, and triple packs and work on any official Rock Band Drum Set from that point forward.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(170,162,'2022-08-03 11:56:52','2022-08-03 11:57:31','Rock Band Microphone',NULL,'The official microphone for Harmonix\'s Rock Band series. ','','','',0,NULL,0),
(171,163,'2022-08-03 12:00:17','2022-08-03 12:10:07','Rock Band 3 Wireless Keyboard',NULL,'The official keyboard controller released in 2010 for Rock Band 3.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(172,164,'2022-08-03 12:12:58','2022-08-03 12:13:42','Rock Band 3 Keyboard Stand',NULL,'Sold separately from the keyboard controller itself, the Rock Band 3 Keyboard Stand allows players to easily play while standing.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(173,165,'2022-08-03 12:15:31','2022-08-03 12:18:17','Tony Hawk Ride Skateboard Controller',NULL,'The Tony Hawk Ride Skateboard Controller is used to simulate riding a skateboard in Tony Hawk Ride and Tony Hawk Shred.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(174,166,'2022-08-03 13:22:20','2022-08-03 13:26:38','PlayStation 3 Memory Card Adaptor',NULL,'The PS3 Memory Card Adaptor allows people to transfer their PS1 and PS2 save files to the PS3 hard drive.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(175,167,'2022-08-03 13:29:51','2022-08-03 13:30:57','Hori Tekken 6 Limited Edition Wireless Fight Stick',NULL,'The Hori Tekken 6 Wireless Fight Stick was part of a limited edition bundle with the game in October 2009.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(176,168,'2022-08-03 13:37:32','2022-08-03 13:40:29','Jabra BT125 Bluetooth Headset',NULL,'The Jabra BT125 Bluetooth Headset was bundled with copies of Warhawk on PS3 to facilitate online play.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(177,169,'2022-08-03 13:57:09','2022-08-03 14:03:54','Wii Nunchuck',NULL,'The official analog stick controller attachment designed by Nintendo for the Wii.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(178,170,'2022-08-03 14:14:48','2022-08-03 14:16:07','Wii Remote Jacket',NULL,'In October 2007, Nintendo introduced a protective cover for the Wii Remote. People who already owned a Wii Remote could order one online for free and all Wii Remotes sold from then on included one.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(179,171,'2022-08-03 14:22:13','2022-08-03 14:22:50','Wii Component Video Cable',NULL,'Nintendo\'s official component cable for the Wii was originally only available through their own website.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(180,172,'2022-08-03 14:45:18','2022-08-04 08:33:28','PlayStation Gold Wireless Stereo Headset',NULL,'Sony\'s official wireless headset for PS4 is supplemented by an app on the console that can fine tune the sound for certain games. Also works with PS3 and Vita.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(181,173,'2022-08-03 14:56:12','2022-08-03 15:01:06','PlayStation Camera for PS4',NULL,'The official PS4 camera allows players to broadcast themselves when streaming, log in to their profile using facial recognition, and use voice activation. It is required for PlayStation VR.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(182,174,'2022-08-03 15:15:34','2022-08-03 15:15:59','Xbox One Controller',NULL,'The official controller designed by Microsoft for the Xbox One.','','','',0,NULL,0),
(183,175,'2022-08-03 15:29:26','2023-10-31 12:07:04','Kinect for Xbox One',NULL,'The second generation Kinect sensor bar was originally included with every Xbox One console.','','','<p>Some controversy was raised when it was announced that the new Kinect would be included and be a mandatory device for any Xbox One to reach full utility. After this announcement did not go well over with fans, the Xbox team backpedaled and eventually dropped the mandate from all future Xbox consoles.</p>',0,NULL,0),
(184,176,'2022-08-03 15:41:29','2023-04-03 17:54:06','Nintendo Switch Pro Controller',NULL,'While a pair of fully featured Joy-Con and a Joy-Con Grip are included with every Nintendo Switch, this is Nintendo\'s official traditional-style controller designed for the system.','','','<p>The <a href=\"/nintendo-switch/3045-157/\" data-ref-id=\"3045-157\">Nintendo Switch</a> Pro Controller features all the same functionality as the <a href=\"/switch-joy-con/3000-101/\" data-ref-id=\"3000-101\">Joy-Con</a> (gyroscope, HD Rumble, NFC sensor) aside from an IR sensor. It is the third \"Pro Controller\" for <a href=\"/nintendo/3010-90/\" data-ref-id=\"3010-90\">Nintendo</a> systems following on from the <a href=\"/wii-u-pro-controller/3000-193/\" data-ref-id=\"3000-193\">Wii U Pro Controller</a> and <a href=\"/wii-classic-controller-pro/3000-192/\" data-ref-id=\"3000-192\">Wii Classic Controller Pro</a>.</p><p> </p><table data-max-width=\"true\"><tbody><tr><td><figure data-align=\"left\" data-size=\"small\" data-img-src=\"https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/original/0/1992/3396739-2786676851-41O7O.jpg\" data-ref-id=\"1300-3396739\" data-ratio=\"0.96355353075171\" data-width=\"439\" data-embed-type=\"image\" style=\"width: 439px\"><a class=\"fluid-height\" style=\"padding-bottom:96.4%\" href=\"https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/original/0/1992/3396739-2786676851-41O7O.jpg\" data-ref-id=\"1300-3396739\"><img alt=\"Standard\" src=\"https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/original/0/1992/3396739-2786676851-41O7O.jpg\" srcset=\"https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/original/0/1992/3396739-2786676851-41O7O.jpg 0w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px\" data-width=\"320\"></a><figcaption>Standard</figcaption></figure></td><td><figure data-align=\"left\" data-size=\"small\" data-img-src=\"https://www.giantbomb.com/a/uploads/original/8/82063/3457055-4007711538-59194.jpg\" data-ref-id=\"1300-3457055\" data-ratio=\"0.96247240618102\" data-width=\"1359\" data-embed-type=\"image\" style=\"